Tom Henderson wrote:

&gt;
&gt; Gerhard,
&gt;
&gt; Yup.  Some important caveats regarding the WRF ESMF component:
&gt;  - It is "experimental" which in WRF lingo means it has not been extensively tested.  I expect that users who attempt to do things much beyond the simple WRF+CPL+SST example will run into difficulties.  The original work was done using earlier versions of ESMF.  We plan to make use of newer ESMF features to improve the WRF component, but have not done so yet.
&gt;  - Coupling communication occurs prior to a WRF time step \(both import and export\).  This is adequate for concurrent coupling in which precise synchronization is not required \(like earlier efforts by John Michalakes, Matthew Bettencourt, Dan Schaffer, and others to couple WRF to ocean models\).  However it is not convenient for sequential coupling when precise synchronization is required.  Fortunately it will be easy to extend the implementation to allow import and export to each occur before or after a WRF time step \(specified at run time\) and I plan to do so.  But this extension is not in WRF 2.2.
&gt;
&gt; Most of these limitations are documented in the WRF 2.2 release -- but not everyone reads documentation...  ;-\)
&gt;
&gt; Regards,
&gt;
&gt; Tom
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; ESMF Support wrote:
&gt;
&gt;&gt; Hi Tom,
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; One more question, does this mean WRF 2.2 works with ESMF 2.2.2r? Can we tell people that have trouble with the WRF/ESMF combo to try WRF 2.2 with ESMF 2.2.2r? Thanks,
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; -Gerhard

